init_text: Following World War III, all the nations of the world agreed to 50 years of strict isolation from one another in order to prevent additional conflicts. 50 years later, the United States comes out of exile, only to learn that no one else went into isolation.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The author takes the reader through a whirlwind of emotions, while keeping the reader on his toes with action and surprises.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The action and surprises are on the mark.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The author takes the reader on a ride in Russia, where an agent will be sent into the city of Moscow.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: It is a mind-boggling account of the state of the city.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: She won over the hearts and minds of many.
